                    Numerical semigroups with the generalized Gorenstein property



Let S be a numerical semigroup and let R be its semigroup ring K[\![S]\!]. We say that S has the generalized Gorenstein property if its semigroup ring has this property. For the definition and characterization of generalized Gorenstein rings please see . 





        s is a numerical semigroup.  The output is true if the semigroup ring K[\![S]\!] is generalized Gorenstein using the characterization by Goto-Kumashiro (). 

gap> s:=NumericalSemigroup(3,7,8);;
gap> IsAlmostSymmetric(s);
false
gap> IsGeneralizedGorenstein(s);
true
